Cell["Updating/replacing", "Subchapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813935326512431*^9, 
  3.8139353309755096`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"85e4dbd4-4675-4954-820d-\
ea6988528fe4"],

Cell["\<\
The goal here is to change the values, more precisely to discretize the data \
using some rule, so transform the values to 0,1. But if you want any other \
change, just adapt the code.  \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813923617498755*^9, 3.813923623512849*^9}, {
  3.813925004437639*^9, 3.8139250265623083`*^9}, {3.8139250604408007`*^9, 
  3.813925075584093*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5aaa432a-0e77-4634-8b26-\
ab1532dd102d"],

Cell["\<\
If values in Column1 < 2 then change to 0, otherwise change to 1
If values in Column2 < 3 then change to 0, otherwise change to 1\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813923626752104*^9, 3.813923696425506*^9}, {
  3.813925028492084*^9, 3.813925053613144*^9}, {3.813933084024536*^9, 
  3.81393308404732*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c59ce06b-8918-4d4a-8d50-\
41b224297837"],

Cell["\<\
To change all values in Column1 of dataset (and Print the new values and the \
index of the For loop), according to the above rule, you can do the following \
code: \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813923877631513*^9, 3.813923884403556*^9}, {
