Cell["\<\
We can do the same for Column3, only remembering of changing the threshold. \
But for what comes next, it is useful to create a two parameter function, one \
parameter representing the threshold:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813947953024063*^9, 3.8139479941974707`*^9}, {
  3.813948274493363*^9, 
